-- LSE enters exclusive talks to acquire Russell Investments
-- 
-- Tue May 20, 2014 02:45AM EDT
-- None



May 20 (Reuters) - London Stock Exchange <LSE.L> said on Tuesday it had entered into exclusive talks with Northwestern Mutual Life Insurance to acquire its asset management and stock index unit, Russell Investments.

Northwestern Mutual started exploring a sale of Russell, which has $259.7 billion (153.94 billion pounds) in assets under management, in January.